class.description:
[GDScriptDecomp] is the core class for working with compiled GDScript bytecode ([code].gdc[/code] and [code].gde[/code] files). Instantiate it pinned to a specific Godot engine version or bytecode revision, then decompile binary bytecode back to readable GDScript source, or compile GDScript source back to bytecode. You can also inspect bytecode metadata and enumerate all supported versions.
Use one of the static factory methods ([method create_decomp_for_version] or [method create_decomp_for_commit]) to create an instance - do not call [code]GDScriptDecomp.new()[/code] directly, because each revision is a distinct subclass.
[codeblock]
var decomp = GDScriptDecomp.create_decomp_for_version("4.3.0")
if decomp == null:
    push_error("No decompiler found for 4.3.0")
    return
var err = decomp.decompile_byte_code("res://scripts/main.gdc")
if err != OK:
    push_error("Decompilation failed: " + decomp.get_error_message())
    return
print(decomp.get_script_text())
[/codeblock]
